#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code prefix ko postfix me convert karne ke liye reverse + stack use karta hai.

1. Prefix expression ko pehle reverse kar dete hain.
2. Ab reversed string ko left se right traverse karte hain.
3. Agar operand mile, to stack me push kar do.
4. Agar operator mile, to stack se top ke 2 operands pop karo:
   - first pop = first operand
   - second pop = second operand
5. Postfix banane ka rule:
   first + second + operator
6. Is new string ko stack me push kar do.
7. End me stack ka top hi final postfix expression hoga.

Main idea:
Prefix: operator operand operand
Postfix: operand operand operator
Isliye reverse karke process karte hain aur operator ko last me laga dete hain.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

class Solution {

    public boolean isOperator(Character a){
        if((a == '+') || (a == '-') || (a == '*') || (a == '/')){
            return true;
        }
        return false;
    }

    public String prefixToPostfix(String s) {
        // Your code goes here
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(s);
        sb.reverse();
        int n = sb.length();
        int i = 0;
        ArrayDeque<String> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();

        while(i < n){
            char ch = sb.charAt(i);
            //if ch is an operator: first + second + operator
            if(isOperator(ch)){
                String first = stack.pop();
                String second = stack.pop();
                String temp = first + second + ch;
                stack.push(temp);
            }
            //if ch is an operand
            else{
                stack.push(Character.toString(ch));
            }
            i++;
        }
        return stack.peek();
    }
}
